# API key for your LLM provider — read ONLY server-side, inside the /api/* functions.
#
# Dry Run works with any OpenAI-compatible endpoint, so use a FREE provider (no
# Anthropic key needed). Pick one, grab a key, and make sure api/_lib/config.ts's
# LLM_BASE_URL + model IDs match it (the default there is Groq):
#
#   Groq (recommended — fast, no credit card):  https://console.groq.com  -> API Keys
#   Google Gemini (AI Studio, no credit card):  https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#   OpenRouter (free models end in ':free'):     https://openrouter.ai/keys
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT prefix this with VITE_. Anything prefixed VITE_ is inlined into
# the client bundle by Vite and would leak the key to the browser. This name has no
# VITE_ prefix on purpose, so it stays server-only.
LLM_API_KEY=
